# GitHub PR Safety

- This rule applies only when the task involves GitHub or pull request actions.
- Never merge a pull request automatically.
- Never enable auto-merge on the user's behalf.
- Never approve and merge on the user's behalf.
- Before any merge action, ask for explicit user confirmation in the current conversation.
- If asked to help with a PR, stop after creating, updating, or reviewing it unless the user explicitly asks to merge.
